node.text:
We sat down with our founder & formulator to chat all things immunity & how the key is getting as many herbs, spices and adaptogens into your routine as possible. 
Want to learn more? Leave questions in the comments below!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Goldthread Plant-Based Tonics on August 24, 2021. May be an image of flower and text that says 'Which Goldthread tonic is best for digestion?'.

node.text:
You asked! Here are our go-to tonics for digestion👇⁣⁣⁠
⁣⁣⁠
🧡✨ Turmeric Radiance: high-quality turmeric & warming spices like cardamom, cinnamon, and coriander help soothe digestion and reduce bloating⁣⁣⁠
💚🍃 Mint Condition: peppermint & spearmint support digestion, while calming lavender & chamomile help ease unwanted digestive discomfort⁣⁣⁠
⁣⁣⁠
Tap our #linkinbio to find where Goldthread is sold near you!⁣ 💛🌱⁠⁣⁣

node.text:
@holisticcocktails is back again with a ✨MUST-TRY MOCKTAIL✨you definitely want to be sipping on this weekend! ⁣
⁣
🍯🌹Honey Rose & Cucumber Mocktail Recipe👇⁣
⁣
🌱 Combine 1/3 oz @herbpharm Lavender Anxiety Soother, 1/3 oz @herbpharm Brain & Memory and 4 oz @drinkgoldthread Honey Rose tonic⁣
🥂 Top with your favorite kombucha⁣
🥒 Add a cucumber wheel for garnish ⁣
⁣
Tag us if you make it & drop a comment with what you’re celebrating!⁣
⁣
(📸: @holisticcocktails) ⁣

Our go-to tonics for relaxation:⁣⁠
Lavender Bliss: hand-picked lavender from the Rhone Valley in France meets a blend of teas and herbs for a soothing wave of natural calm.⁣ ⁠
Mint Condition: mountain tea and mint from the hills of Greece refreshes and soothes with fresh-squeezed lemon for a refreshing end to any stressful day.⁣ ⁠
Tap our #linkinbio to learn more!⁣ 💜🌱⁠
#DrinkMorePlants ⁣⁠

node.text: Mint Condition 🌱 Inspired by the beautiful Greek islands, the cool, crisp and refreshing plants in Mint Condition are full of antioxidants and phytonutrients which help improve and support overall vibrant health and longevity. Mint has long been used throughout various cultures as a reliable way to improve digestive health and create feelings of wellbeing. #DrinkMorePlants
